com.outsideinsdk
Interface ExportProperties

public interface ExportProperties

ExportProperties provides all of the properties and their values that are valid for use in an Export object. The naming convention for the ExportProperties constants is as follows:

PROPERTY - any constant using an un-separated name represents a valid Property name.
PROPERTY_VALUE - any constant using a separated name constisting of a PROPERTY name and some VALUE represents a valid VALUE for its respective PROPERTY.

Special Cases:

DEFAULT - can be used to represent the default VALUE for any PROPERTY.
PROPERTY_U - any constant with a VALUE name of U indicates the use of an encoded VALUE. These constants are for internal use, and should not be set on a Properties passed to Export.setRuntimeProperties.
